  "prompt": "What are some Yu-Gi-Oh! Apps?",
  "response": "As of the latest data, some popular Yu-Gi-Oh! apps include:\n\n1. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Links** - This is one of the most popular Yu-Gi-Oh! apps, offering quick and engaging duels with simplified rules and a vast library of cards. Players can duel against others online with their favorite characters from the series.\n\n2. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Neuron** - This app serves as an official companion tool for Yu-Gi-Oh! trading card game players. It features card search, deck building, and life point tracking functionalities.\n\n3. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Legacy of the Duelist: Link Evolution** - Available on various platforms including mobile devices, this game offers a comprehensive dueling experience covering different generations of the Yu-Gi-Oh! universe.\n\n4. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Generation** - Although this game is not regularly updated, it allows players to enjoy casual duels with a large collection of cards spanning many sets.\n\n5. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Carnival** - Although mainly popular on Nintendo 3DS, this is another Yu-Gi-Oh! title that some players enjoy for its unique take on the card game mechanics.\n\nRemember to check the respective app stores for availability and compatibility with your device, as the availability of apps might vary by region and platform.",
